TECHNICAL REGULATIONS OF THE RUSAF INDOOR CHAMPIONSHIP, ALL-RUSSIAN INDOOR COMPETITIONS
from 02/14/2021 8:40 PM
February 15-17, 2021,
arena of the CSKA exercise club, Moscow, Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1
The day of arrival is February 14, 2021, the day of departure is February 18, 2021.
AGE OF PARTICIPANTS, TEAM AND INDIVIDUAL COMPETITIONS, ADMISSION CONDITIONS
Individual competitions with a team standings, athletes from the teams of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation participate, in the same age group - men, women.
Athletes of younger age groups are allowed to participate in sports competitions among men and women (born in 1998) if they have the necessary sports qualifications.
Athletes admitted to competitions only in the individual competition do not participate in the distribution of points in the team competition.
The results for athletes who did not take part in these competitions are not counted, and points for the team standings are not awarded.
All teams whose athletes perform in accordance with the approved territorial affiliation are awarded team points in full.
Participating organizations are allowed to add two athletes to the team in excess of the quota to participate in each type of relay race.
In the relay race, team members must perform in a sports uniform of the same color.
In case of violation of this paragraph of the regulations, the team may not be allowed to compete.
In the relay race, athletes can compete only for the team of one territory.
Athletes with a category not lower than the 1st sports category are allowed to compete.
Athletes declared by the teams of the regions, who have passed a medical examination and received a doctor's permission are allowed to participate in the competition.
Applications for the competition are accepted only through the unified information system of the All-Russian Athletics Federation.
The deadline for submitting applications for the competition is February 12, 2021 at 18.00 Moscow time.
The Commission for the Admission of Participants and for the confirmation of applications sent in advance and the provision of the necessary documents on the application will work on February 14 from 10:00 to 16:00 in the arena of the CSKA Exercise Club, in the lobby of the conference hall, 3rd floor, at the address: Leningradsky Prospekt, 39, building 1.
All athletes, coaches and representatives of the teams included in the application are required to take educational anti-doping online courses on the official website of RUSADA and receive a certificate before the start of the competition.
ATHLETES, COACHES, REPRESENTATIVES ARE OBLIGED TO SUBMIT TO THE SECRETARIAT A CERTIFICATE WITH A NEGATIVE RESULT OF THE PSR TEST FOR SSOUS-19, WITH THE DATE OF BIOMATERIAL COLLECTION NO LATER THAN 72 HOURS FROM THE MOMENT OF APPEARANCE AT THE CREDENTIALS COMMISSION.
The territorial affiliation of athletes is determined in accordance with the Unified Information System and the decision of the Commission on Transitions.
Official training in the competitive arena on February 14 from 16:00 to 19:00. On competition days - outside the competition time.
The pre-start warm-up is held on the ground, under the guidance of senior judges for disciplines.
Collection and registration of participants will be held in the registration area (Sai Koot).
SaY Koot will be located behind the second turn next to the shot put sector.
When registering, the participant is obliged to demonstrate to the judge the appropriately fixed bib number.
The exit of participants from the place of registration to the places of competition in technical sports is carried out under the guidance of the senior referee / referee for the sport, in running sports - under the guidance of the assistant starter.
Leaving the place of competition without the permission of the referee is prohibited.
Registration of participants in running sports begins 40 minutes and ends 10 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration in technical types begins 50 minutes and ends 25 minutes before the start of the event.
Registration in the pole vault begins 80 minutes and ends 55 minutes before the start of the event.
Participants who do not appear for registration are not allowed to participate in the competition.
Participants are provided with trial attempts in accordance with the Rules of the sport.
In the 60 m race and the 60 m hurdles, competitions are held in 3 rounds, the exit to the next round will be determined at the end of the acceptance of applications.
In the 200 m, 400 m, 800 m races, competitions are held in 2 rounds, reaching the final in time.
In case of equality of results in running sports when entering the next round, equality is resolved in the following way: 1. Checking the results with an accuracy of 1/1000; 2. If equality remains after the application of paragraph 1, the drawing of lots shall be held.
In the 1500 m, 3000 m, 5000 m 4x400 m races, the final races are held.
In jumping and throwing, qualification (in case of more than 16 declared athletes) and final competitions are held, for participation in which it is necessary to qualify.
If the number of participants who have fulfilled the standard is less than 12 people, then athletes get to this number in accordance with the best qualification results.
If a participant declared in several types of the program did not appear for one of the types without a valid reason, then he is not allowed to compete in subsequent types.
Athletes are allowed to use personal equipment, provided that these equipment are approved by the Organizing Committee.
The athlete must hand over personal equipment (shot) for inspection to the equipment service (inventory room in the warm-up area) no later than 2 hours before the start of the event.
During the competition, it is not allowed to replace equipment.
In case of equality of results when determining the winner in vertical jumps, a jump is carried out.
All protests and appeals shall be filed in accordance with the Rules – Rule 8 (146).
An oral protest is made by the representative/athlete immediately after the announcement of the result that caused the protest.
A written appeal is submitted no later than 30 minutes after the official announcement of the result for this type.
Protests and appeals regarding the right of athletes to participate in competitions or their affiliation with a particular team are submitted in the same manner to the appeals jury.
The results of the team competition are determined in accordance with the Regulations. The results of the All-Russian competitions are accepted into the team standings.
The winner and prize-winners of competitions in running sports are obliged to appear independently at the award department located in the arena no later than 10 minutes after the end of the event.
Prize-winners of the championship are awarded medals of the championship, prize-winners of all-Russian competitions (200 m and 5000 m)
Any athlete who does not start in a running or technical form is not allowed to participate in subsequent events, and it is considered that he has stopped participating in the competition.
If an athlete advances to the next round after the preliminary round of the competition, but then did not compete in this type of program, he will be suspended from participating in further types of competitions, including the relay.
In the event that the athlete submits medical documents on the impossibility of participating in any type of competition, by the decision of the technical delegate, he can be admitted to participate in other disciplines of the competition, but only on the next day.
During the competition, the doctor is located in the area provided by the organizers.
The technical meeting of GSK with official representatives of the teams will be held on February 14 at 18:00 in the conference hall of the arena of the LFC CSKA.
The meeting of the members of the GSK with the panel of judges of the competition will be held on February 14 at 18:40 in the conference hall of the arena of the LFC CSKA.
