ADELE'S EXTRAORDINARY ADVENTURES
The most dashing adventure movie of the decade hints that "The Extraordinary Adventures of Adele" will begin as "Amélie", rush towards <Jurassic Park", continue with "Indiana Jones" and "The Mummy", and end with "Titanic".
The film is based on the first volume of Jacques Tardy's comics about journalist Adele Blanc-Sec.
Louise Bourgoin starred in only three films before Adèle.
The actress became famous for her role in The Girl from Monaco, for which she was nominated for a César Award.
The director does not run after the viewer with an outstretched hand, begging him to evaluate special effects, scenery or tricks, but carries him along, like an old-fashioned novelist who exclaims before a big journey to the center of the earth or to the end of the world: "Forward, my reader, great things await us!"
At the same time, Besson treats genre cinema, about which he knows absolutely everything, unceremoniously and cheerfully, like a boy who has seen enough old films and read Jules Verne.
