Zuckerberg is obsessed with the idea of popularity and leadership, but what is more about his business - positive or negative?
And what are the social consequences of his invention?
Is he a swindler?
Or a cunning manipulator?
Fincher and Sorkin will never close the book if there is even the slightest hint of something like this in it.
But you don't even have to do it here: in their version of history, it doesn't matter at all.
"How does it feel to feel beautiful?" asks Tre WeaNez's song "WaBu Uots'te A Vsp Map," which precedes the credits.
