Somnologist named the causes of sleep problems
Somnologist Sofia Cherkasova spoke about foods and habits that interfere with healthy sleep.
As the specialist noted, sleep problems often arise due to products containing caffeine.
We are talking primarily about tea, coffee, chocolate and any desserts containing cocoa.
Their use before bed should be limited, since they not only interfere with falling asleep, but also make sleep "torn", which means that it does not allow the body to fully recover.
According to the doctor, it is better to stop using caffeine-containing products 6-8 hours before bedtime.
Otherwise, they contribute to a decrease in the excitability threshold of the nervous system and, as a result, there are difficulties with falling asleep.
Alcohol also negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
The doctor clarifies that small doses of alcoholic beverages promote relaxation and do not affect sleep.
However, amounts exceeding 36 grams in terms of pure alcohol lead to various sleep disorders, such as light sleep and frequent nighttime awakenings.
In addition, to prevent problems with falling asleep, the somnologist recommends giving up spicy food in large portions.
Large amounts and spicy foods contribute to an increase in core body temperature, which negatively affects the ability to fall asleep.
For healthy sleep, it is necessary not only to observe the external temperature regime: the optimal air temperature is 18-20 degrees, but also the absence of increased body temperature.
According to Cherkasova, you should not abuse heavy food before going to bed, since it will not allow the body to fully recover and rest: it will be forced to spend energy on digestion.
The doctor also recalled that the lack of healthy sleep and accumulated lack of sleep affect the quality of life and usual activities, so it is extremely important to adhere to a sleep and rest schedule and allow the body to recover.
