Fitness expert spoke about working out outside in winter for weight loss
Fitness expert called walks in winter a great way to lose weight without intense loads
Fitness expert Anthony Yeung spoke about effective outdoor interval training for weight loss.
His words are quoted by the portal Eat This, Not That.
The specialist called active walks in winter a great way to lose weight without intense loads, as well as improve the state of the cardiovascular system and psychological health.
"For the first five to ten minutes, walk at a normal pace to warm up your body and joints.
Then walk as fast as you can for one minute without running.
One minute at a normal pace," Yeung explains.
It is necessary to do three approaches.
Next, the specialist advises to do lunges or squats with weights for 15 seconds, after which walk at a comfortable speed for another 45 seconds.
You need to repeat this sequence five times. Then Yeung suggests alternating between an active step (two minutes) and a calm step (one minute) three more times.
You need to complete the walk with a five-minute walk at a calm pace and a few stretching exercises.
In total, this workout will take 35 minutes outdoors.
Earlier, master of sports in athletics Maxim Babenko-Kudryavtsev in a comment to Lenta.ru gave advice on choosing equipment for winter jogging.
"You will need thermal underwear, moisture-wicking things, special light but warm hats.
Shoes for running in winter are distinguished by denser materials, a higher platform and a tread of the sole," the athlete said.
