Users of the marketplace received a notification according to which buyers who need a package will have to pay from 6 to 15 rubles for it.
This amount will be debited from the card specified in your personal account.
As indicated in the company, the corresponding step will help reduce the use of plastic and contribute to the preservation of nature.
As follows from the appendix to the offer for the provision of services for the delivery of parcels to individuals, the contractor, that is, the person who opened the pick-up point, must provide packages free of charge at the request of the client.
At the same time, they must be decorated in certain colors and have the agreed image.
Packages are purchased at the expense of the owners of pick-up points, if this obligation is not fulfilled, a fine of 10000 rubles is imposed on them for each violation.
Earlier, Wildberries customers caught the site debiting funds from cards, the data of which had previously been deleted from their personal account.
As buyers fear, this comes with great security risks.
The support service, in turn, explained that this is provided for by the user agreement.
As follows from it, the company has the right to write off money from remote cards without notifying the client if payment from others does not go through for one reason or another.
The company, commenting on the situation, said that settlements with customers are carried out with the permission of customers, and no leakage of bank card data can occur.
